root: ^Twinkle: Heya, honey. You've got some spare parts? I'm in need of a tune-up and a fresh coat of paint. Can you fit me in?

Intercom: ^Yeah, Twinkle, I have spares from your last tune-up.
Sure: ^Twinkle: Gorgeous, love. I'll be right in.
Spares: ^Twinkle: That's why I like you, you're reliable like that. Not a lot of people are reliable like you are anymore, it's a very unreliable business in an unreliable city.
Twinkle: ^Twinkle enters. They look fatigued. The city has definitely gotten to them.
